# Styling, design tokens, and map components

This project does **not** use Tailwind. Use **design tokens**, **CSS Modules**, and **`pageTypography`** helpers so UI stays consistent and CMS-driven pages match the rest of the site.

## Tokens (source of truth)

- Edit JSON under **`tokens/`** (`tokens/color.json`, `tokens/font.json`).
- Run **`npm run tokens:build`** to regenerate (also runs automatically before `npm run build` and `npm run build-storybook`).
- [Style Dictionary](https://amzn.github.io/style-dictionary/) outputs **`src/styles/generated/tokens.css`** as `:root` CSS variables. **Do not hand-edit** the generated file — change the JSON and rebuild.
- **Never hardcode hex values or font strings.** Always use the corresponding CSS custom property.

### Available tokens

```css
/* Semantic surfaces */
--color-page-bg: #e8e8e8       /* body / page background */
--color-section-bg: #f5f5f5    /* section / panel backgrounds */
--color-card-bg: #ffffff       /* card / surface backgrounds */

/* Typography */
--color-heading: #4f4f4f       /* h1–h6 */
--color-documented-body: #000000
--color-documented-prose-body: #374151
--color-documented-prose-heading: #111827

/* Interactive */
--color-link: #0000ff
--color-link-hover: #0000cc

/* Gray scale */
--color-custom-50: #f9f9f9
--color-custom-100: #f0f0f0
--color-custom-200: #e8e8e8
--color-custom-300: #d1d1d1
--color-custom-400: #b8b8b8
--color-custom-500: #9f9f9f
--color-custom-600: #868686
--color-custom-700: #6d6d6d
--color-custom-800: #545454
--color-custom-900: #3b3b3b

/* Typography */
--font-work-sans: 'Work Sans', sans-serif
--font-mono: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, 'Liberation Mono', 'Courier New', monospace
```

## Wiring

- **`src/app/globals.css`** imports generated tokens first, then defines base typography, links, layout helpers (skip links, `.prose`, `.sr-only`), and small global utilities.
- Use **`var(--color-…)`** and other token variables in CSS Modules or globals — never raw values.

## Components and pages

- Colocate **`ComponentName.module.css`** with the component or route; import as `styles` and use `className={styles.foo}`.
- **`src/lib/pageTypography.ts`** re-exports classes from **`src/styles/pageTypography.module.css`** for shared shells and body copy. Pick the right stack per page type (see **Hub page layout** below).
- Storybook stories may use small **`*.stories.module.css`** files for layout-only wrappers.
- **Design system first**: Before creating new UI, look for an existing component/pattern (atoms/molecules/organisms, existing tool pages, table/map shells, etc.) and reuse it. Prefer extracting a shared component/style when a pattern repeats across routes.

## Hub page layout (CMS + static hubs)

**Default for new content pages** (`/lab`, `/case-studies`, CMS `[slug]` routes like `/about`, `/reading-list`):

| Piece | Export / component |
|-------|-------------------|
| Shell | `pageShellBg` + `hubPageWrap` |
| Header | `HubPageHeader` |
| Body | `pageProse` + `PortableText` |
| Sections below body | `ReadingList`, `SpeakingEngagements`, etc. (`margin-top: 2.5rem`) |

**Do not** use `pageBanner` / `pageTitleH1` / `pageBodyTypography` for new hub-style pages — that legacy stack adds excessive top padding and title gaps.

**Data / tool pages** (Strava, eBird, TripIt) keep `PageHeroWithDataSource` + `pageBodyTypography` — see Storybook **Organisms/Examples/ToolPage**.

Canonical reference: Storybook **Organisms/Examples/HubPage** (`HubPageExample.stories.tsx`). Chromatic visual regression runs against these stories.

## Map components (Dynamic/Static split)

MapLibre-backed components **must** use a three-file split to avoid SSR errors:

```
FooMap.tsx          ← actual MapLibre component (client-only, 'use client')
FooMapDynamic.tsx   ← next/dynamic wrapper with ssr: false
FooMapLoading.tsx   ← server-rendered loading skeleton (no MapLibre imports)
```

**Always import `FooMapDynamic` in page components**, never `FooMap` directly. The loading skeleton renders on the server and is replaced client-side once MapLibre initialises.

Example pattern:
```tsx
// FooMapDynamic.tsx
import dynamic from 'next/dynamic'
import { FooMapLoading } from './FooMapLoading'

export const FooMapDynamic = dynamic(() => import('./FooMap'), {
  ssr: false,
  loading: () => <FooMapLoading />,
})
```

Shared map chrome (spinner, aspect-ratio shell) lives in `src/components/maps/MapLoadingShell`.

## Atomic design structure

```
src/components/
  atoms/       # Button, Chip, ListGroupHeading
  molecules/   # PortableText, PostCard, ResourceGroup, ResourceListItem,
               # ResourceMetaChips, PageHeroWithDataSource
  organisms/   # Footer, ReadingList, SpeakingEngagements
  strava/      # StravaRunsMap, StravaRunsTable, RunsMapTableSkeleton
  backyard/    # BackyardBirdMap, BackyardObservationsTable
  travel/      # FlightPathMap
  maps/        # MapLoadingShell (shared map chrome)
  ui/          # Headless/utility (DataTable, Typography stories)
  utils/       # LazyMount
```

